Here’s how commenting works in each of the listed languages — both single-line and multi-line (block) comments where applicable:

1. Python

# This is a single-line comment

"""
This is a
multi-line comment (commonly used as a docstring)
"""


2. PHP

// This is a single-line comment

# This is also a single-line comment

/*
This is a 
multi-line comment
*/


3. MATLAB

% This is a single-line comment

%{
This is a
multi-line comment
%}


4. Java

// This is a single-line comment

/*
This is a 
multi-line comment
*/


5. C#

// This is a single-line comment

/*
This is a 
multi-line comment
*/


6. C++

// This is a single-line comment

/*
This is a 
multi-line comment
*/


